<p>Today I&#8217;m launching a new podcast called 15 Minutes In Hell &#8212; a 15-minute-long interview show featuring interesting people in tech, business, entertainment, sports, and any other area I see fit. </p><p>You&#8217;ll be able to subscribe through <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/ed-zitrons-15-minutes-in-hell/id1701465453">Apple Podcasts</a>, PocketCasts, and <a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/6NfYJcdXmhQuAHYZhvsmWE?si=72f56af9d2624b77">Spotify</a> in the coming days. I&#8217;ll update this post as and when I get links. In the meantime, you can manually add the feed to your preferred podcast app using <a href="https://api.substack.com/feed/podcast/8982.rss">this link</a>.&nbsp;If you like the show, <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/ed-zitrons-15-minutes-in-hell/id1701465453">please do review it on Apple Podcasts</a>.</p><p>Today&#8217;s guest is Ben Collins, Senior Reporter at NBC, who you can find on<a href="https://twitter.com/oneunderscore__/status/1651593528718290946"> Twitter</a> and<a href="https://bsky.app/profile/bencollins.bsky.social"> Bluesky</a>. We talked about Elon Musk and how Ben manages to keep empathetic while covering the worst people in the world.&nbsp;</p>